description: Defying expectations of chaos and violence, unexpectedly large crowds turned out to vote.
title: Long Lines Form as Egyptians Vote in Historic Election
title_page: Long Lines Form as Egyptians Vote in Historic Election - The New York Times
maintext:
Slide 1 of 10,
Voters waited to cast their ballots on Monday, as unexpectedly large crowds turned out in Egypt’s first parliamentary election since the ouster of President Hosni Mubarak, a ballot that seemed to blend vindication of the democratic struggle with uncertainty over the revolution’s final outcome.
